associated_activity_logs.name: ${target_initials_upper} Phone Screen
associated_activity_logs.extra_log_types:
_definitions:
  enabled_if: &enabled_if

    # if performed a phone screening no consent to continue, disable after 14 days
    not_all_not_interested:
      any:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
          select_is_good_time_to_speak: not interested
          select_may_i_begin: not interested
          select_still_interested: 'no'

      all_created_at:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
          created_at:
            condition: <
            value: -14 days

    # if recorded a withdraw activity, disable after 14 days
    not_all_withdraw:
      any:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals:
          select_subject_withdrew_reason: withdrew
          select_investigator_terminated:
            - yes - due to ae
            - yes - other reason
          lost_to_follow_up_no_yes: 'yes'
          no_longer_participating_no_yes: 'yes'
      all_created_at:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals:
          created_at:
            condition: <
            value: -14 days

    # if performed a screening follow up and not eligible, disable after 14 days
    not_all_ineligible:
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings:
        eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no: 'no'
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

    # if performed a screening follow up and not interested in participating, disable after 14 days
    not_all_ps_followup_not_interested:
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings:
        still_interested_blank_yes_no: 'no'
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

    # if the exit survey has been completed, disable after 14 days
    not_all_complete:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments:
        extra_log_type: follow_up_surveys
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys:
        select_survey_type: exit survey
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

  # Rule for editable_if only
  # Lock the forms on finalization
  not_finalized: &not_finalized
    not_any:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens:
        extra_log_type: finalize


  ####
  # Boilerplace for notifying roles
  # Override the subject: and if: structures to refine operation
  ####

  # Default email - just add roles or users
  notify_email_default: &notify_email_default
    type: email
    layout_template: ${target_initials_lower} notification layout
    content_template: ${target_initials_lower} inex message
    subject: "${target_initials_upper} App: Phone Screen Complete"


  # Default SMS - just add roles or users
  notify_sms_default: &notify_sms_default
    type: sms
    layout_template: standard sms layout
    content_template: ${target_initials_lower} sms notification
    subject: "${target_initials_upper} Phone Screen Complete"



  # MedNav reviewer
  notify_reviewer: &notify_reviewer
    <<: *notify_email_default
    role: email - inex reviewer

  # MedNav reviewer SMS
  notify_reviewer_sms: &notify_reviewer_sms
    <<: *notify_sms_default
    role: sms - inex reviewer

  # PI
  notify_pi: &notify_pi
    <<: *notify_email_default
    role: email - inex pi


  # PI SMS
  notify_pi_sms: &notify_pi_sms
    <<: *notify_sms_default
    role: sms - inex pi


_default:
  showable_if: *enabled_if
  creatable_if: *enabled_if
  editable_if: *not_finalized
  save_action:
    on_create: create_next_creatable


################################################
start_phone_screen:
  label: Start Phone Screening
  fields:

  references:
    dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screening:
      from: this
      add: one_to_this

  caption_before:
    all_fields: Record initial screening responses. If necessary, enter a date and time to follow up.
    submit: If the subject is ready to continue, save this form and continue with the next form.
  view_options:
    show_embedded_at_top: true

  creatable_if:
    <<: *enabled_if
    not_any:
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
        select_still_interested: "yes"


  save_action:
    on_create:
      create_next_creatable:
        if:
          all:
            dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
              select_still_interested: "yes"
              id:
                this_references: id
      show_panel:
        value: activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments
        if:
          not_all:
            dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
              select_still_interested: "yes"
              id:
                this_references: id
      hide_panel:
        value: activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens
        if:
          not_all:
            dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
              select_still_interested: "yes"
              id:
                this_references: id

  showable_if:
    always: true

  save_trigger:
    on_create:

      create_reference:

        - activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment:
            if:
              all:
                dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
                  id:
                    this_references: id
                this:
                  any:
                    dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
                      select_is_good_time_to_speak:
                        - left voicemail
                        - not appropriate time
                      select_still_interested: 'yes - call back'

            in: master
            with:
              extra_log_type: schedule_screening
              select_who: current_user_email
              follow_up_when:
                dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
                  id:
                    this_references: id
                  follow_up_date: return_value
              follow_up_time:
                dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
                  id:
                    this_references: id
                  follow_up_time: return_value
              notes: Phone screen call when to voicemail or participant requested a call back
              select_record_from_player_contacts:
                activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments:
                  extra_log_type: schedule_screening
                  select_record_from_player_contacts: return_value




################################################
schedule_callback:
  label: Schedule Callback
  fields:
    - callback_date
    - callback_time
    - notes
  caption_before:
    all_fields: |
      Thank you for your patience and for answering these previous questions.

       We will then contact you to let you know if you are eligible or not. If you are eligible, we will let you know the next steps.

       Do you have any questions?

       We will call you back to inform you of your eligibility status. What is a good day/time to call you? It may take up to 10 days for us to make a determination.


    submit: If you have any questions in the meantime, please do not hesitate to contact us. Thank you again for your time.

  creatable_if:
    <<: *enabled_if
    all:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens:
        extra_log_type: start_phone_screen
    not_any:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens:
        extra_log_type: schedule_callback


  save_trigger:
    on_create:

      create_reference:

        - activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment:

            in: master
            with:
              extra_log_type: screening_follow_up
              select_who: current_user_email
              follow_up_when:
                this:
                  callback_date: return_value
              follow_up_time:
                this:
                  callback_time: return_value
              notes: Participant phone screening completed. Follow-up has been scheduled.
              select_record_from_player_contacts:
                activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments:
                  extra_log_type: schedule_screening
                  select_record_from_player_contacts: return_value


################################################
finalize:
  label: Finalize Entries
  caption_before:
    all_fields: |
      When finalized the phone screen forms are locked from editing.
    submit: |
      Save this entry to lock the phone screen forms and generate an inclusion/exclusion checklist record.
      Click the cancel button instead if review or revision of the phone screen forms is still required.
  creatable_if:
    <<: *enabled_if
    all:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens:
        extra_log_type: schedule_callback
    not_any:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens:
        extra_log_type: finalize


  # Override the default that hides activities after a certain stage,
  # so that any user can see that the phone screen process has been completed
  showable_if:
    always: true


  save_action:
    on_create:
      show_panel:
        value: activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_inex_checklists
      hide_panel:
        value: activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens

  save_trigger:
    on_create:
      create_reference:
        - activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_inex_checklist:
            in: master
            with:
              extra_log_type: phone_screen_review


  # Notify the reviewers that the phone screen has been completed
      notify:
        - *notify_reviewer
        - *notify_reviewer_sms
#        - *notify_pi
#        - *notify_pi_sms

associated_activity_logs.name: Medical Navigation
associated_activity_logs.extra_log_types:
_definitions:
  enabled_if: &enabled_if

    # if performed a phone screening no consent to continue, disable after 14 days
    not_all_not_interested:
      any:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
          select_is_good_time_to_speak: not interested
          select_may_i_begin: not interested
          select_still_interested: 'no'

      all_created_at:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings:
          created_at:
            condition: <
            value: -14 days

    # if recorded a withdraw activity, disable after 14 days
    not_all_withdraw:
      any:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals:
          select_subject_withdrew_reason: withdrew
          select_investigator_terminated:
            - yes - due to ae
            - yes - other reason
          lost_to_follow_up_no_yes: 'yes'
          no_longer_participating_no_yes: 'yes'
      all_created_at:
        dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals:
          created_at:
            condition: <
            value: -14 days

    # if performed a screening follow up and not eligible, disable after 14 days
    not_all_ineligible:
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings:
        eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no: 'no'
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

    # if performed a screening follow up and not interested in participating, disable after 14 days
    not_all_ps_followup_not_interested:
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings:
        still_interested_blank_yes_no: 'no'
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

    # if the exit survey has been completed, disable after 14 days
    not_all_complete:
      activity_log__${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments:
        extra_log_type: follow_up_surveys
      dynamic_model__${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys:
        select_survey_type: exit survey
        created_at:
          condition: <
          value: -14 days

  ref_filestore_container: &ref_filestore_container
    nfs_store__manage__container:
      from: this
      add: one_to_this
      view_as:
        edit: hide
        show: filestore
        new: not_embedded

  save_trigger:
    on_create_filestore_container: &create_filestore_container
      create_filestore_container:
        name: general files
        label: General Files
        create_with_role: nfs_store group 600

    - activity_date
    - select_direction
    - select_contact
    - select_result
    - select_next_step
    - follow_up_when
    - follow_up_time

    - select_contact

    - select_result

    - follow_up_time

        select_activity:
          - schedule follow up
          - completed
    select_next_step:
      any:
        select_result: follow up
        select_activity: schedule follow up
    follow_up_when:
      any:
        select_result: follow up
        select_activity: schedule follow up
    follow_up_time:
      any:
        select_result: follow up
        select_activity: schedule follow up
    select_direction:
      not_any:
        select_activity:
          - schedule follow up
          - completed
    select_contact:
      not_any:
        select_activity:
          - completed
          
        select_direction:
          - in person

        field_type: select_record_from_player_contacts

    select_direction:
      edit_as:
        alt_options:
          "In Person": in person

associated_reports.name: Ready for Sign Off - PI
associated_reports.description: Participants with inclusion / exclusion checklist ready for sign off by PI
associated_reports.sql:
SELECT
   dt.master_id,
   tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
   --pi.first_name,
   --pi.last_name,
   dt.source,
   dt.extra_log_type activity,
   dt.communication_result,
   dt.checklist_signed,
   dt.exit_type,
   dt.created_at,
   dt.r
FROM (

  SELECT
    di.*,
    dlo.exit_type,
    rank()
    OVER (
    PARTITION BY di.master_id
    ORDER BY di.created_at DESC
    ) AS r
  FROM
  (
    SELECT
      al.master_id,
      'tracker' "source",
      al.extra_log_type,
      CASE WHEN
        (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up') THEN 'follow up'
      WHEN
        (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed') THEN 'completed'
      ELSE
        al.select_result 
      END "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      al.created_at

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al

    WHERE
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up')
    OR
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed')
    OR
    'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' is not null AND 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
    OR
    'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' is not null AND 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
    OR
    (
      al.extra_log_type IN ('inex-phone-screen-finalized', 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi', 'withdraw', 'perform_screening_follow_up')
    )

    UNION

    SELECT
      inex.master_id,
      'inex' "source",
      inex.extra_log_type,
      NULL "communication_result",
      inex.signed_no_yes "checklist_signed",
      inex.created_at


    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_inex_checklists inex
    WHERE

    (
      (
        'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-baseline-complete' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_baseline'
      ) 
      
      
      OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' IS NOT NULL AND (
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'
        OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-baseline-complete' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_baseline'
      ) 
    ) 

    UNION

    SELECT
      ps.master_id,
      'phone screen' "source",
      'phone_screen_finalized' "extra_log_type",
      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      ps.created_at


    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens ps
    WHERE

    ('inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'phone-screen-complete' OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' IS NOT NULL AND 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi'  = 'phone-screen-complete' )
    AND extra_log_type IN ('finalize')



    

  ) AS di

  LEFT OUTER JOIN (

    SELECT
      master_id,
      'not interested or ineligible (follow up)' "exit_type"


    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings ps
    WHERE
      still_interested_blank_yes_no = 'no' OR
      eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no = 'no'


    UNION

    SELECT
      master_id,
      'not interested (phone screening)' "exit_type"

    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings inits
    WHERE
     select_is_good_time_to_speak = 'not interested' OR
     select_may_i_begin = 'not interested' OR
     select_still_interested = 'no'

    UNION

    SELECT
      master_id,
      'withdrew' "exit_type"

    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals wd
    WHERE
     select_subject_withdrew_reason = 'withdrew' OR
     select_investigator_terminated IN ('yes - due to ae', 'yes - other reason') OR
     lost_to_follow_up_no_yes = 'yes' OR
     no_longer_participating_no_yes = 'yes'

     UNION

    SELECT
      master_id,
      'completed exit survey' "exit_type"
    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys surv
    WHERE
      select_survey_type = 'exit survey'
  ) dlo ON dlo.master_id = di.master_id

) AS dt

inner join player_infos pi on dt.master_id = pi.master_id
inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments ${target_initials_lower} on dt.master_id = tbs.master_id

WHERE
('inex-phone-screen-so-pi' IS NULL OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' IS NOT NULL AND r = 1)
AND
(

  'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'general-follow-up' AND dt.extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='follow up'
  OR
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'general-completed' AND dt.extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='completed'
  OR 
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
  OR 
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
  OR 
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
  OR 
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'

  OR (
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'inex-baseline-complete'
    AND (
      dt.extra_log_type IN ('sign_baseline') AND
      checklist_signed = 'yes'
    )
  )
  OR (
    'inex-phone-screen-finalized' = 'phone-screen-complete'
    AND (
      dt.extra_log_type IN ('phone_screen_finalized')
    )
  )
  OR 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' NOT IN ('inex-complete', 'phone-screen-complete') AND dt.extra_log_type = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized'
)
AND (
  'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' IS NULL
  OR NOT (
    r = 1
    AND (
      'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'general-follow-up' AND dt.extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='follow up'
      OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'general-completed' AND dt.extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='completed'

      OR 
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
      OR 
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
      OR 
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
      OR 
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND dt.extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'

      OR (
          'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'inex-baseline-complete'
          AND (
            dt.extra_log_type IN ('sign_baseline') AND
            checklist_signed = 'yes'
          )
      )

      OR (
        'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' = 'phone-screen-complete'
        AND (
          dt.extra_log_type IN ('phone_screen_finalized')
        )
      )
      OR 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' NOT IN ('inex-complete', 'phone-screen-complete') AND dt.extra_log_type = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi'
    )
  )

)
AND (
  'in_study' IS NULL 
  OR (
    'in_study' = 'in_study' AND dt.exit_type IS NULL
    OR
    'in_study' = 'not_in_study' AND dt.exit_type IS NOT NULL
  )
)
ORDER BY
  dt.created_at DESC
;

  -- a previous item

  SELECT
    di.*,
    dlo.exit_type,

    ) AS r
  FROM

    --
    -- ${target_initials_upper} Tracker process
    --

      al.extra_log_type,
      CASE WHEN
        (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up') THEN 'follow up'
      WHEN
        (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed') THEN 'completed'
      ELSE
        al.select_result

      NULL "checklist_signed",
      al.created_at

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al

    WHERE
      'appointment-set' = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up')
      OR 'appointment-set' = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed')
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
      OR al.extra_log_type IN ('appointment-set', :activity_outstanding)

    UNION

    --
    -- ${target_initials_upper} Tracker process for appointments
    --
    SELECT
      al.master_id,

      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al

    INNER JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_appointments apt
    ON al.master_id = apt.master_id

    WHERE
      'appointment-set' = 'appointment-set' AND al.extra_log_type='appointment'
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'appointment-set' AND al.extra_log_type='appointment'

    UNION
    --
    -- Inclusion / Exclusion process
    --
    SELECT
      inex.master_id,
      'inex' "source",
      inex.extra_log_type,
      NULL "communication_result",
      inex.signed_no_yes "checklist_signed",
      inex.created_at


    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_inex_checklists inex

    WHERE

    (
      (
        'appointment-set' = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
        OR 'appointment-set' = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'

        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-tms-so' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_tms_eligibility'
      )
    )

    UNION

    --
    -- Phone Screen process
    --
    SELECT
      ps.master_id,

      'phone_screen_finalized' "extra_log_type",
      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",

pi.first_name, pi.middle_name, pi.last_name, pi.nick_name,
a.street, a.street2, a.city, a.state, a.zip, 
pc.data, pc.rec_type
from masters m
inner join player_infos pi
on pi.master_id = m.id 
inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments b

left join addresses a
on m.id = a.master_id

or pi.first_name ~* :name

    AND pi.last_name ~* coalesce(split_part(:name, ' ', 2),'none')
  )
) OR
(
regexp_replace(pc.data, '\W+', '', 'g') ~* regexp_replace(:name, '\W+', '', 'g')
) OR
(
b.${target_initials_lower_us}_id::varchar = :name

associated_reports.name: ${target_initials_upper} Outstanding Activities
associated_reports.description: Search for records where one activity has been performed and another hasn't been performed after it (optional).
associated_reports.sql:
SELECT
   dt.master_id,
   tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
   --pi.first_name,
   --pi.last_name,
   dt.source,
   dt.extra_log_type activity,
   dt.communication_result,
   dt.checklist_signed,
   dt.exit_type,
   dt.created_at,
   dt.r
FROM (
  -- Generate a resultset of ranked results
  -- with most recently created items first
  -- that include only the requested previous and outstanding activities
  -- This allows us to see if an outstanding item appears more recently than
  -- a previous item

  SELECT
    di.*,
    dlo.exit_type,
    rank()
    OVER (
    PARTITION BY di.master_id
    ORDER BY di.created_at DESC
    ) AS r
  FROM
  (
    --
    -- ${target_initials_upper} Tracker process
    --
    SELECT
      al.master_id,
      'tracker' "source",
      al.extra_log_type,
      CASE WHEN
        (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up') THEN 'follow up'
      WHEN
        (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed') THEN 'completed'
      ELSE
        al.select_result
      END "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      al.created_at

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al

    WHERE
      :activity_performed = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='follow up' OR select_activity = 'schedule follow up')
      OR :activity_performed = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general' AND (select_result='completed' OR select_activity = 'completed')
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'general-follow-up' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'general-completed' AND al.extra_log_type='general'
      OR al.extra_log_type IN (:activity_performed, :activity_outstanding)

    UNION

    --
    -- ${target_initials_upper} Tracker process for appointments
    --
    SELECT
      al.master_id,
      'tracker' "source",
      al.extra_log_type,
      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      '1900-01-01 00:00:00'

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al

    -- INNER JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_appointments apt
    -- ON al.master_id = apt.master_id

    WHERE
      :activity_performed = 'appointment-set' AND al.extra_log_type='appointment'
      OR :activity_outstanding is not null AND :activity_outstanding = 'appointment-set' AND al.extra_log_type='appointment'

    UNION
    --
    -- Inclusion / Exclusion process
    --
    SELECT
      inex.master_id,
      'inex' "source",
      inex.extra_log_type,
      NULL "communication_result",
      inex.signed_no_yes "checklist_signed",
      inex.created_at


    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_inex_checklists inex

    WHERE

    (
      (
        :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-baseline-complete' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_baseline'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-tms-responses' AND extra_log_type = 'tms_responses'
        OR :activity_performed = 'inex-tms-so' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_tms_eligibility'
      )


      OR :activity_outstanding IS NOT NULL AND (
        :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-baseline-complete' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_baseline'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-tms-responses' AND extra_log_type = 'tms_responses'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-tms-so' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_tms_eligibility'
      )
    )

    UNION

    --
    -- Phone Screen process
    --
    SELECT
      ps.master_id,
      'phone screen' "source",
      'phone_screen_finalized' "extra_log_type",
      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      ps.created_at

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_phone_screens ps

    WHERE
      (:activity_performed = 'phone-screen-complete' OR :activity_outstanding IS NOT NULL AND :activity_outstanding  = 'phone-screen-complete' )
      AND extra_log_type IN ('finalize')



    UNION

    --
    -- Navigation process
    --
    SELECT
      master_id,
      'navigation' "source",
      extra_log_type,
      NULL "communication_result",
      NULL "checklist_signed",
      coalesce(event_date + start_time, created_at) "created_at"

    FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_navigations nav

    WHERE
    (
      (
        :activity_performed = 'has-planned-event' AND extra_log_type = 'planned_event'
        OR :activity_performed = 'has-event-feedback' AND extra_log_type = 'station_event'
      )

      OR :activity_outstanding IS NOT NULL AND (
        :activity_outstanding  = 'has-planned-event' AND extra_log_type = 'planned_event'
        OR :activity_outstanding = 'has-event-feedback' AND extra_log_type = 'station_event'
      )
    )


  ) AS di

  LEFT OUTER JOIN (
    -- Add an exit type column for those participants that have exited the study
    -- NULL if they are still in the study

    --
    -- Phone Screen not interested or not eligible
    --
    SELECT
      master_id,
      'not interested or ineligible (follow up)' "exit_type"


    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings ps
    WHERE
      still_interested_blank_yes_no = 'no' OR
      eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no = 'no'


    UNION

    --
    -- Phone screen not interested
    --
    SELECT
      master_id,
      'not interested (phone screening)' "exit_type"

    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings inits
    WHERE
     select_is_good_time_to_speak = 'not interested' OR
     select_may_i_begin = 'not interested' OR
     select_still_interested = 'no'

    UNION

    --
    -- Withdrew
    --
    SELECT
      master_id,
      'withdrew' "exit_type"

    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_withdrawals wd
    WHERE
     select_subject_withdrew_reason = 'withdrew' OR
     select_investigator_terminated IN ('yes - due to ae', 'yes - other reason') OR
     lost_to_follow_up_no_yes = 'yes' OR
     no_longer_participating_no_yes = 'yes'

     UNION

    --
    -- Completed study
    --
    SELECT
      master_id,
      'completed exit survey' "exit_type"
    FROM ${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys surv
    WHERE
      select_survey_type = 'exit survey'

  -- End left outer join
  ) dlo ON dlo.master_id = di.master_id

-- End ranked selection
) AS dt

-- Include player details
inner join player_infos pi on dt.master_id = pi.master_id
-- Match ${target_initials_upper} ID to master_id
inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments ${target_initials_lower} on dt.master_id = tbs.master_id

WHERE
(
  -- Either:
  -- no outstanding activity has been selected, so just perform a plain query
  -- or:
  -- we want the first record from the results based
  -- on an order of most recently created appearing first (and therefore overriding older records)
  :activity_outstanding IS NULL OR :activity_outstanding IS NOT NULL AND r = 1
)
AND
(
  -- Based on the activity performed selection pick the appropriate conditions
  :activity_performed = 'general-follow-up' AND extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='follow up'
  OR :activity_performed = 'general-completed' AND extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='completed'
  OR :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
  OR :activity_performed = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'

  OR :activity_performed = 'appointment-set' AND extra_log_type='appointment'

  OR (

    AND (

    )
  )

  OR :activity_performed NOT IN ('inex-complete', 'phone-screen-complete') AND extra_log_type = :activity_performed
)
AND (
  -- If no outstanding activity was selected then there are no conditions to apply
  :activity_outstanding IS NULL

    -- An outstanding activity was selected
    -- Based on the activity outstanding selection pick the appropriate conditions
    -- that the first record in the results must match in order to correctly override the previous activities

    r = 1

      :activity_outstanding = 'general-follow-up' AND extra_log_type='general' AND dt.communication_result='follow up'

      OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-finalized' AND extra_log_type = 'finalize_phone_screen_checklist'
      OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-pi' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen'
      OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-mednav' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_reviewer'
      OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-phone-screen-so-staff' AND extra_log_type = 'sign_phone_screen_staff'
      OR :activity_outstanding = 'inex-tms-responses' AND extra_log_type = 'tms_responses'

      OR :activity_outstanding = 'phone-screen-complete' AND extra_log_type = 'phone_screen_finalized'

      OR (

associated_reports.name: ${target_initials_upper} In Process & Exited
associated_reports.description: All subjects that have joined or exited the study: in process (phone screening scheduled), completed, withdrawn, ineligible, not interested (during phone screen or follow-up)
associated_reports.sql:
SELECT * from (
SELECT distinct dt.master_id, tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id, 
CASE 
WHEN extra_log_type = 'follow_up_surveys' THEN 'completed'
WHEN extra_log_type = 'withdraw' THEN 'withdrawn'
WHEN ps_interested1 = 'not interested' OR ps_interested2 = 'not interested' OR ps_still_interested = 'no'
  THEN 'not interest during phone screening'
WHEN extra_log_type = 'perform_screening_follow_up' AND eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no = 'no'
  THEN 'ineligible'
WHEN extra_log_type = 'perform_screening_follow_up' AND follow_up_still_interested = 'no'
  THEN 'not interest during screening follow-up'
WHEN extra_log_type = 'schedule_screening' THEN 'in process'
ELSE extra_log_type
END "status", 
--pi.first_name, pi.last_name ,
dt.created_at "when"
-- , ps_interested1, ps_interested2, ps_still_interested
FROM 
(
SELECT
al.master_id, al.created_at, al.extra_log_type,
${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings.eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no, ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings.still_interested_blank_yes_no "follow_up_still_interested", 
${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_is_good_time_to_speak "ps_interested1",
${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_may_i_begin "ps_interested2",
${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_still_interested "ps_still_interested",
rank()
 OVER (
  PARTITION BY al.master_id 
  ORDER BY al.created_at DESC
 ) AS r

FROM activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al
LEFT JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings
ON al.master_id = ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings.master_id
LEFT JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys
ON al.master_id = ${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys.master_id
LEFT JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings
ON al.master_id = ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.master_id
WHERE
(
(
  ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_is_good_time_to_speak = 'not interested' 
  OR ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_may_i_begin = 'not interested'
  OR ${target_initials_lower_us}_ps_initial_screenings.select_still_interested = 'no'
)
OR
(
  extra_log_type = 'perform_screening_follow_up'
  AND ( 
    ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings.eligible_for_study_blank_yes_no = 'no'
    OR ${target_initials_lower_us}_screenings.still_interested_blank_yes_no = 'no'
  )
)
OR
(
  extra_log_type = 'follow_up_surveys'
  AND ${target_initials_lower_us}_surveys.select_survey_type = 'exit survey'
)
OR
(
  extra_log_type = 'withdraw'
)
OR
(
  extra_log_type = 'schedule_screening'
)
)
) dt
INNER JOIN player_infos pi
ON dt.master_id = pi.master_id
INNER JOIN ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments tbs
  ON dt.master_id = tbs.master_id
WHERE r = 1 
) dt2
WHERE status IN(:select_status)
ORDER BY status, "when" desc
;

    label: Select / de-select statuses to report

    default:

      - not interest during screening follow-up
    selections: 
      ineligible: ineligible
      completed: completed
      withdrawn: withdrawn

associated_reports.description: View all scheduled calls, communication follow-ups, phone screenings and planned assessment events in a chronological list, split week by week.
associated_reports.sql:
create temp table nav_events
as select
'' "-",
al.event_date,
al.start_time,
pi.master_id,
ipa.${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
pi.first_name,
pi.last_name,
al.extra_log_type,

al.select_event_type,
al.other_event_type,
al.completion_time,
al.arrival_time,
al.select_navigator,
al.select_pi,
al.location
from
activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignment_navigations al
inner join player_infos pi
on pi.master_id = al.master_id
inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments tbs
on tbs.master_id = al.master_id

where
(:from_date IS NULL or event_date >= :from_date)
AND (:to_date IS NULL or event_date <= :to_date)
AND ((:type) IS NULL or extra_log_type in (:type))
AND ((:confirmed) IS NULL or select_status in (:confirmed))
AND ((:station) IS NULL or select_station in (:station))
AND (:${target_initials_lower_us}_id IS NULL or tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id = :${target_initials_lower_us}_id)
;


create temp table appointments
as select
visit_start_date,
ap.master_id,
ipa.${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
pi.first_name,
pi.last_name,
max(ap.id) appointment_id
from ${target_initials_lower_us}_appointments ap
inner join activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments al
on al.master_id = ap.master_id

inner join player_infos pi
on ap.master_id = pi.master_id

inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments tbs
on tbs.master_id = al.master_id


where
  visit_start_date IS NOT NULL
  AND (:from_date IS NULL or visit_start_date >= :from_date)
  AND (:to_date IS NULL or visit_start_date <= :to_date)
  AND (:${target_initials_lower_us}_id IS NULL or tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id = :${target_initials_lower_us}_id)
GROUP BY
ap.master_id, visit_start_date, pi.first_name, pi.last_name, tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id
;

create temp table scheduled_calls
as select
  dt.follow_up_when,
  dt.follow_up_time,
  dt.master_id,
  tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
  p.first_name,
  p.last_name,
  dt.extra_log_type,
  dt.select_who
from
  (
    select a.master_id,
      a.extra_log_type,
      a.select_who,
      a.follow_up_when,
      a.follow_up_time,
      a.notes,
      rank()
    OVER (
      PARTITION BY a.master_id, a.extra_log_type
      ORDER BY a.created_at DESC
    ) AS r

    from activity_log_${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments a
    where
      follow_up_when is not null
      AND (:from_date IS NULL OR follow_up_when >= :from_date)
      AND (:to_date IS NULL OR follow_up_when <= :to_date )
  ) dt
inner join player_infos p
  on dt.master_id = p.master_id

inner join ${target_initials_lower_us}_assignments tbs
  on dt.master_id = tbs.master_id

WHERE r = 1
AND (:${target_initials_lower_us}_id IS NULL or tbs.${target_initials_lower_us}_id = :${target_initials_lower_us}_id)
;

create temp table all_dates
as
select event_date from nav_events
union
select follow_up_when from scheduled_calls
union
select visit_start_date from appointments
;

SELECT
  al.event_date "date",
  al.start_time "start time",
  'assessment event' "-",
  al.extra_log_type "type",
  select_navigator "assigned to",
  select_pi "assigned to pi",
  al.master_id,
  al.${target_initials_lower_us}_id "${target_initials_upper} ID",
  --al.first_name "first name",
  --al.last_name "last name",
  al.select_status "status",
  al.select_station "station",
  al.select_event_type "event type",
  al.other_event_type "other event type",
  al.location,
  al.completion_time "planned or actual completion time",
  al.arrival_time "arrival time"

FROM nav_events al

UNION

SELECT
  date_trunc('week', dd)::date,
  NULL,
  '          ',
  '          ',
  '          ',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  --'          ',
  --'          ',
  '          ',
  '          ',
  '          ',
  '          ',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL
FROM generate_series
      ( (select min(event_date)::timestamp from all_dates)
      , (select max(event_date)::timestamp from all_dates)
      , '7 day'::interval) dd

UNION

SELECT
  visit_start_date event_date,
  NULL,
  'appointment start',
  '',
  '' "assigned to",
  '' "assigned to pi",
  master_id,
  ${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
  --first_name,
  --last_name,
  '',
  '',
  '',
  '',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL
FROM appointments

UNION

SELECT
  follow_up_when,
  follow_up_time,
  'scheduled call' "-",
  extra_log_type,
  select_who "assigned to",
  '' "assigned to pi",
  master_id,
  ${target_initials_lower_us}_id,
  --first_name,
  --last_name,
  '',
  '',
  '',
  '',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL
FROM scheduled_calls


order by
"date",
"start time"
;

associated_message_templates.name: ${target_initials_lower} ps intro overview
associated_message_templates.template:
As you may know, The Football Players Health Study is a research initiative dedicated to understanding the current health and well-being of former NFL players. The purpose of the in-person assessments is to learn more about the long-term health effects of a career in professional football.

Participation will involve a 2 day study visit in Boston that includes assessments of areas such as pain and physical function, memory/thinking/problem solving, sleep, heart function, and brain imaging. All nights will be spent in a local hotel. The visits will take place at various Harvard-affiliated institutions. Throughout the study, a member of the study team will guide you through all of the visits. All transportation, meal and lodging costs will be covered by the Study.

By participating, you will be helping us better understand player health. Additionally, you will also have the opportunity to learn more about yourself as we will be providing some results from the clinical assessments at the end of the study. At the participants request, these can be shared with a health care provider for further guidance and interpretation.

I am going to go over the study in some more detail. If you have any questions while I explain the study please stop me and ask. Do you have any questions so far?

associated_message_templates.name: ${target_initials_lower} ps intro details
associated_message_templates.template:
INTERVIEWER: HAVE THE CONSENT FORM ON HAND TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL DETAILS ABOUT THE STUDY VISITS AS NEEDED.

Day 0

Our team will coordinate your arrival to Boston to arrive the day before the study begins. Your first night will be spent in a local hotel.

Day 1

Day 1 will begin at MGH where you will review the consent form with a study physician and study coordinator. Any specific questions you have will be answered then. You will then go through a DEXA scan, which is similar to an x-ray but looks at bone density. Next, you will have your blood drawn and go through a general assessment of your health similar to a physical at a doctors appointment. You will have to fast prior to this blood draw. In the afternoon, you will go through two PET scans, a sense of smell test and a test of your sensory responses. The day will end around 6pm.

  • Consent review: The first day will start with a review of the consent. You will meet with a study coordinator and the study physician in order to review the study assessments and the consent form. During this time, you will be able to ask any questions or voice any concerns you may have.
  • DEXA: Once you have agreed to participate, you will undergo a DEXA scan. A DEXA scan is similar to an x-ray, but it is a scan that looks at bone density and body composition.
  • OGTT: You will then get your blood drawn. Please note that will ask that you do not eat for at least 8 hours prior to this blood draw we will be sure to remind you when you arrive. You will have breakfast following the blood draw.
  • During the rest of the first day you will:
    • Undergo an assessment of your health such as a review of your medical history, medications, and a brief physical exam that includes body composition measures (e.g. height, weight, waist size)
    • Fill out some questionnaires about your health
    • PET (Positron Emission Tomography) with CT (Computed Tomography) PET/CT scans take pictures of what is going on inside the body using special dyes with radiation that light up inside the body to make a picture. The scanner is shaped like a big ring and you will be positioned on your back on the scanner table. The table may move forward and backward as part of the testing the procedures. You will complete two different PET scans.
    • Sense of smell testing (olfactory) This brief test consists of breathing different odors from a small handheld odor delivery device and being asked questions about your familiarity, memory and ability to name each odor.
    • Sensory testing An assessment that consists of tests to measure your sensory responses for example, having pressure applied to different parts of your body or putting you hand in ice water you will be asked to report when these sensations are uncomfortable.
  • The first study night will be spent in the hotel.

Day 2

On the second full study day, you will begin with neuropsychological testing. After this, you will have an MRI of your brain and your liver. In the afternoon, you will travel to a different hospital to do physical functioning testing. After physical functioning, you will go through our TMS and EEG assessment. TMS is noninvasive and uses magnetic fields to measure connectivity in the brain. The day will end at the hotel where you will be set up for the sleep assessment. You will sleep with various sensors on your body to analyze your sleeping patterns.

  • Neuropsychological testing An assessment that consists of tests that evaluate your mood, memory and how you think, learn and solve problems. This will be conducted with a trained neuropsychologist.
  • MRI (Magnetic resonance imaging) of your brain and liver This is a scan that takes pictures of your brain and liver using a large magnet and radio signals.
  • Physical function testing Testing that consists of a series of tests such as lifting weights, a timed walking test, walking upstairs carrying weights, walking while doing another task (simple math), and testing your balance. These assessments will be administered and overseen by a trained exercise physiologist.
  • TMS (Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation) and EEG (Electroencephalogram) The TMS will measure brain plasticity. Brain plasticity is the ability of the brain to change and learn through experience. TMS is a noninvasive way of stimulating the brain. TMS uses a magnetic field to cause activity in the brain. The magnetic field is produced by a coil that is held next to your scalp. In this study, we will use TMS to create activity in your brain and will measure your brains response to the activity. This is how we measure brain plasticity. During the TMS assessment, you will have a series of electrodes (small round discs) will be placed on your head and your brain waves will be measured while you sit quietly and then while you complete a few simple tasks on a computer.
  • Sleep study During the second night, you will have a sleep study in your hotel room. This will include having sensors placed on your body to monitor your movement, heart rate, breathing and brain waves while you sleep. A trained technician will assist you in placing various sensors on your body, but they will leave you for the night. Additionally, you will be asked to complete several questionnaires on your sleep habits.

Day 3

On the third and final study day, you will begin with cardiac testing and then X-rays. After you have completed all of the assessments, we will be returning some preliminary results from your testing. Our medical navigation nurse will meet with you and discuss some of the results. Some results will be reported to you in the coming weeks and that process will be explained to you at that time.

  • Cardiac testing This testing consists of activities such as having pictures taken of your heart (ultrasound), assessment of your resting metabolic rate which will include you having to wear light headgear with a breathing tube, and a bicycle exercise test.
  • X-rays You will undergo an X-ray exam, where you will be asked several questions, prepped and asked to stand in the equipment for the duration of the scan.
  • Results Return At the end of your last day we are going to go over some of the results that we collected so that you have something to take away

Are you still interested in hearing more about the study or do you have any questions at this time?

Would you be willing to answer questions about your health and medical history to find out if you might qualify for the study? This should take about 30 minutes and you will receive a $20 gift card for your time. Do you have time now to continue?

associated_message_templates.name: ${target_initials_lower} eligibility call eligible 2
associated_message_templates.template:
Would you like me to review the details about the study again?

The study will take place at multiple hospitals in the Boston area over 2 1/2 days with overnight stays at a local hotel. Each day will consist of different testing. You will be provided with your personal study visit schedule ahead of your visit. You will be given breaks and meals throughout the days.

You will be assigned a study navigator, a member of the Football Players Health Study staff, who will accompany you throughout each day of the study. The navigator will assure that you get to each test. They will also handle scheduling issues or conflicts and provide assistance and act as a resource to you throughout the study.

Your mornings will begin between 5-7am and will end around 6-7pm, depending on the schedule for that particular day. Each day will begin with a review of that days schedule and any questions you may have will be answered. Each day will end with a review of how the procedures went. We may contact you after you complete the study visit with additional questions and follow-up.

The first day of the study a study navigator will greet you and a study physician will review the consent form with you and help to answer any questions that you have. A nurse practitioner will conduct a baseline physical exam and collect information about your health and medical history. Over the next two and a half days, you will undergo assessments such as PET/CT scans, sense of smell test, neuropsychological testing, MRI scans, physical function assessments, TMS and EEG, an overnight sleep study, cardiac testing, pain assessments, and an X-ray exam.

Compensation up to $1800 will be given to you for your time and efforts involved in participating in this study. In order to pay you, you will need to provide your Social Security Number (SSN) or Individual Taxpayer Identification Number (ITIN). Your payment will be processed 30 days after the study visit. You will need to fill out a W9 and any other pertinent tax information in order to receive payment.

Just as a reminder, we will cover the costs of your transportation, (parking), lodging and meals during the study visit. (ask where they are coming from)

Do you have any questions?

Thank you for your time today.

We will send you additional study information to review and our travel partners will be contacting you to make arrangements for your visit to Boston.

Please feel free to contact us at any time should you have any questions.

END CALL
